Program: Discovery
Title: The Story Of Aids - origins
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryjw
Last Broadcast Date: 03 November 2003
Allan Little explores the origins of HIV/Aids. In the second of a series of programme he traces the subsequent progress of the virus across the world. This programme begins in the 1980s. The discovery of a form of Aids which infected monkeys helped provide a breakthrough.